    "Many of our favorite movies are based on books, but often, the adaptation doesn’t quite live up to the original. Books provide depth and detail that movies sometimes skip, while movies bring stories to life with visuals and pacing, immersing you in a way words on a page can’t. Which is better: the book that allows your imagination to run wild, or the movie that brings a story to life on the screen?",
